209 inline double ReadLikelihood::GetMvaValue__( const std::vector<double>& inputValues ) const
210 {
211  double ps(1), pb(1);
212  std::vector<double> inputValuesSig = inputValues;
213  std::vector<double> inputValuesBgd = inputValues;
214  for (size_t ivar = 0; ivar < GetNvar(); ivar++) {
215 
216  // dummy at present... will be used for variable transforms
217  double x[2] = { inputValuesSig[ivar], inputValuesBgd[ivar] };
218 
219  for (int itype=0; itype < 2; itype++) {
220 
221  // interpolate linearly between adjacent bins
222  // this is not useful for discrete variables (or forced Spline0)
223  int bin = int((x[itype] - fHistMin[ivar])/(fHistMax[ivar] - fHistMin[ivar])*fNbin[ivar]) + 0;
224 
225  // since the test data sample is in general different from the training sample
226  // it can happen that the min/max of the training sample are trespassed --> correct this
227  if (bin < 0) {
228  bin = 0;
229  x[itype] = fHistMin[ivar];
230  }
231  else if (bin >= fNbin[ivar]) {
232  bin = fNbin[ivar]-1;
233  x[itype] = fHistMax[ivar];
234  }
235 
236  // find corresponding histogram from cached indices
237  float ref = (itype == 0) ? fRefS[ivar][bin] : fRefB[ivar][bin];
238 
239  // sanity check
240  if (ref < 0) {
241  std::cout << "Fatal error in ReadLikelihood: bin entry < 0 ==> abort" << std::endl;
242  std::exit(1);
243  }
244 
245  double p = ref;
246 
247  if (GetType(ivar) != 'I' && !fHasDiscretPDF[ivar]) {
248  float bincenter = (bin + 0.5)/fNbin[ivar]*(fHistMax[ivar] - fHistMin[ivar]) + fHistMin[ivar];
249  int nextbin = bin;
250  if ((x[itype] > bincenter && bin != fNbin[ivar]-1) || bin == 0)
251  nextbin++;
252  else
253  nextbin--;
254 
255  double refnext = (itype == 0) ? fRefS[ivar][nextbin] : fRefB[ivar][nextbin];
256  float nextbincenter = (nextbin + 0.5)/fNbin[ivar]*(fHistMax[ivar] - fHistMin[ivar]) + fHistMin[ivar];
257 
258  double dx = bincenter - nextbincenter;
259  double dy = ref - refnext;
260  p += (x[itype] - bincenter) * dy/dx;
261  }
262 
263  if (p < fEpsilon) p = fEpsilon; // avoid zero response
264 
265  if (itype == 0) ps *= p;
266  else pb *= p;
267  }
268  }
269 
270  // the likelihood ratio (transform it ?)
271  return TransformLikelihoodOutput( ps, pb );
272 }
273 
274 inline double ReadLikelihood::TransformLikelihoodOutput( double ps, double pb ) const
275 {
276  // returns transformed or non-transformed output
277  if (ps < fEpsilon) ps = fEpsilon;
278  if (pb < fEpsilon) pb = fEpsilon;
279  double r = ps/(ps + pb);
280  if (r >= 1.0) r = 1. - 1.e-15;
281 
282  if (true) {
283  // inverse Fermi function
284 
285  // sanity check
286  if (r <= 0.0) r = fEpsilon;
287  else if (r >= 1.0) r = 1. - 1.e-15;
288 
289  double tau = 15.0;
290  r = - log(1.0/r - 1.0)/tau;
291  }
292 
293  return r;
294 }
